{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Rock|type2=Ice}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Rock|prevnum=698|prev=Amaura|nextnum=700|next=Sylveon}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Aurorus\n|jname=アマルルガ\n|tmname=Amaruruga\n|category=Tundra\n|ndex=699\n|karea=Coastal\n|kdex=067\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Rock\n|type2=Ice\n|height-ftin=8\'10"\n|height-m=2.7\n|weight-lbs=496.0\n|weight-kg=225.0\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Refrigerate\n|abilityd=Snow Warning\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Monster\n|gendercode=31\n|eggcycles=30\n|evtotal=2\n|evhp=2\n|expyield=104\n|lv100exp=1,000,000\n|color=Blue\n|catchrate=45\n|body=08\n|pokefordex=aurorus\n|generation=6\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Aurorus\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'アマルルガ\'\'\' \'\'Amaruruga\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Rock|Ice}} [[Fossil]] {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VI]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Amaura}} when [[level]]ed up at [[Time|night]] starting at level 39, after it is revived from a [[Sail Fossil]].\n\n==Biology==\nAurorus is a quadruped, dinosaurian Pokémon that resembles a {{wp|sauropoda|sauropod}}. It is primarily blue with a lighter blue underside. It has bright blue eyes, a long neck, and a long, tapering tail with a teardrop-shaped tip. On its head is a V-shaped white marking with single, light blue crystal in the center. Two large, flowing sails extend from the top of its head and run down the length of its neck. The sails are pale whitish-yellow at the base and fade into a pale bluish-purple at the edges. However, its sails can change color depending on its mood as seen in [[ Pokémon-Amie]]. Running the length of its body on either side is a line of small ice crystals. There are three clawed toes on its hind legs, but one large nail and a single claw on its forelegs.\n\nAurorus is usually kindly in nature, but has the ability to create ice walls or encase enemies in ice. The crystals on its body produce freezing air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit (-150 degrees Celsius).\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Aurorus anime.png|thumb|250px|left|Aurorus in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===Major appearances===\nAurorus debuted in \'\'[[XY023|Coming Back into the Cold!]]\'\' alongside its pre-evolved form. Both Pokémon were brought back to life after being found frozen in ice. It reappeared in the newspaper in \'\'[[XY027|To Find a Fairy Flower!]]\'\'.\n\n===Minor appearances===\nA fossil of an Aurorus appeared in \'\'[[SM001|Alola to New Adventure!]]\'\', where it was seen in the [[Pokémon School]].\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Grant Aurorus Adventures.png|thumb|left|150px|Aurorus in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nIn \'\'[[PAXY17|Shooting Frogadier]]\'\', [[Grant]] was shown with an Aurorus. After several minor appearances, it was used during the attempt to stop the [[ultimate weapon]] from activating.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Aurorus (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=rock|type2=ice}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=067|label1=Coastal|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as {{tt|-240 degrees Fahrenheit|-150 degrees Celsius}}, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=Using its diamond-shaped crystals, it can instantly create a wall of ice to block an opponent\'s attack.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as {{tt|-240 degrees Fahrenheit|-150 degrees Celsius}}, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|t=FFF|v=Alpha Sapphire|entry=Using its diamond-shaped crystals, it can instantly create a wall of ice to block an opponent\'s attack.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|num1=246|label1={{gameabbrev7|USUM}}:|reg2=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Pokémon Sun and Moon|Sun, Moon]], [[Pokémon: Let\'s Go, Pikachu! and Let\'s Go, Eev