anging sails are also based on {{wp|aurora}}s, most likely aurora borealis due to its partial Ice typing, and the fact it only evolves at night, when the aurora borealis is most often seen. Similar to Tyrantrum, considering its white, V-shaped mark with an ice crystal covering the top of its head and two flowing extended sails running down its neck, it may have also been based upon a {{wp|queen}}, with the mark and the two flowing sails acting as a tiara or a headdress worn by queens from medieval times while its body with small ice crystals resembles a dress.\n\n====Name origin====\nAurorus may be a combination of \'\'aurora\'\' and \'\'Amargasaurus\'\'.\n\nAmaruruga is from \'\'Amargasaurus\'\'.\n\n==In other languages==\n{{Other languages|type=Rock|type2=Ice\n|ja=アマルルガ \'\'Amaruruga\'\'|jameaning=From \'\'{{wp|Amargasaurus}}\'\'\n|fr=Dragmara|frmeaning=From \'\'dragon\'\' and \'\'Amargasaurus\'\'\n|es=Aurorus|esmeaning=Same as English name\n|de=Amagarga|demeaning=From \'\'Amargasaurus\'\' and possibly \'\'{{wp|Caves of Gargas|Gargas}}\'\'\n|it=Aurorus|itmeaning=Same as English name\n|ko=아마루르가 \'\'Amarureuga\'\'|komeaning=From its Japanese name\n|zh_cmn=冰雪巨龍 \'\'Bīngxuějùlóng\'\'|zh_cmnmeaning=From {{tt|冰雪 \'\'bīngxuě\'\'|snow and ice}}, {{tt|巨 \'\'jù\'\'|gigantic}}, and {{tt|恐龍 \'\'kǒnglóng\'\'|dinosaur}}\n|zh_yue=冰雪巨龍 \'\'Bīngsyutgeuihlùhng\'\'|zh_yuemeaning=From {{tt|冰雪 \'\'bīngsyut\'\'|snow and ice}}, {{tt|巨 \'\'geuih\'\'|gigantic}}, and {{tt|恐龍 \'\'húnglùhng\'\'|dinosaur}}\n|hi=औरोरस \'\'Aurorus\'\'|himeaning=Transcription of English name\n|ru=Аврорус \'\'Avrorus\'\'|rumeaning=Transcription of English name\n}}\n{{-}}\n\n==Notes==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Rock|type2=Ice}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Rock|prevnum=698|prev=Amaura|nextnum=700|next=Sylveon}}\n|}\n{{Project Pokédex notice}}\n\n[[Category:Fossil Pokémon]]\n\n[[de:Amagarga]]\n[[es:Aurorus]]\n[[fr:Dragmara]]\n[[it:Aurorus]]\n[[ja:アマルルガ]]\n[[zh:冰雪巨龙]]'}